//filter()
1. The filter Method (The "Sieve")
filter is used to select specific elements based on a condition (Predicate).

Goal: To reduce the number of elements in the stream.

Input: A function that returns true or false.

Result: A stream containing only the items that returned true.

Data Type: The type of the objects remains the same (e.g., a Stream of Student stays a Stream of Student).
